text: Arjan Knipping (born 1 August 1994) is a Dutch swimmer specialising in 200 and 400 metre individual medley. Knipping holds the Dutch national record on the 200 and 400 metre medley. == Career == He represented the Netherlands at the 2019 World Aquatics Championships and reached the finals in both the 200 and 400 metre individual medley, setting a new national record in both events. With these results he also qualified for the 2020 Summer Olympics in Tokyo, Japan.
